$ SQL: table constraints

A *table constraint* enforces an *integrity rule* on a → development/databases/SQL/table.

The → misc/ISO/9075[SQL standard] specifies four table constraints:
  • → development/databases/SQL/table/constraint/primary-key[Primary key] constraint
  • Unique constraint
  • Referential constraint
  • Check Constraint

A table constraint is
  • either *enforced* or *not enforced*
  • either *deferrable* or *not deferrable*

sa:
  → misc/ISO/9075/F383[SQL Standard feature F383: Set column `not null` clause]
